<m0>more than 32 countries. It is based in New York and has about 1,000 employees.<ep>
  Global Financial Information Corp., owned by the venture-capital firm Welsh, Carson, Anderson & Stowe, provides real-time and historical data on more than 300,000 stocks, options, commodities, futures, indexes and currencies.<ep>
  ``GFI will be an excellent new home for Knight-Ridder Financial,'' said Polk Laffoon, Knight-Ridder vice president for corporate relations. ``Their different expertises dovetail very well.''<ep>
  Knight-Ridder said it plans to use the proceeds mainly to reduce debt and repurchase stock. Subject to regulatory approval, the sale is expected to be completed in the third quarter.<ql>
